<br>
Initially I agreed with the idea of a Ragefire list. It seemed honorable enough, however due to recent events I am 100% against it as it stands. I speak for myself and not my guild. This opinion may be due to misinformation. If this is the case, please post and I may or may not correct that opinion depending on the information provided.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr>   The answer does not lie in the &quot;List&quot;. It lies in changing the end of this epic yet again.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Players have no choice over the matter. This is entirely up to VI. Because of this we have been forced to deal with a somewhat ill-managed list (where is the link for that thing anyway?).<br>
<br>
I have a RL friend who is about 30-40th in line for the epic camp. This position in line fluctuates on a weekly basis according to him. We talk about every other week and often the list and his frustration with it comes up at least once. He keeps getting bumped down because other people are *magically added* above him, like they have some kind of right to the spawn ahead of him. Shantily, Peqi, Klarge, and various other people (I point these three out because they are the only ones I remember, but it was 8+) who have been added/moved ahead of my friend (who shall remain unknown to all but the observant). WHY?<br>
<br>
This is supposed to be a fair list, yet when personal friends or other people are bumped on the list ahead of others who have been waiting for god knows how long for their shot at the camp, well that is WRONG plain and simple.<br>
<br>
I admit I am not privy to the address of The List (tm) however if my conversations with my friend are accurate this is not an honorable way to do this.<br>
<br>
How to make it fair:<br>
<br>
*You cannot sell your spot on the ragefire list.<br>
*You cannot trade places with someone on the ragefire list. If you give your spot up then at least be a wo/man and go to the end.<br>
*You cannot BUMP someone ahead of other people simply because they are you best personal buddy in the whole wide world (or they bribed you or whatever).<br>
<br>
Questions about the list:<br>
<br>
1) Did the events above actually happen? I do trust my friend however I want to hear the other side of the story.<br>
2) If this did happen, WHY did it happen? Can you give any fair reason to people who are being treated like second class citizens and being made to sit at the back of the preverbial bus so other &quot;better&quot; people can crawl in ahead of them? If this did not happen, ignore this question.<br>
3) If you were stranded on a desert island with a pipe cleaner and a 5'' floppy disk, how would you get off?<br>
<br>
